cc:Work.dc:title: Box - SideHingeBox
cc:Work.dc:description:
Box, with an hinge that does not protrude from the back of the box, and a latch.
This box is another take on a hinge box. The hinges doesn't protrude from the box, but the sides needs double walls. When opened, 2 sides are opening, improving access inside the box. An optional latch is included, based on a mechanical switch and a 3D printed button. The latch is one-way: the box can be closed freely (this side of the button is angled, and totally smooth since it's the printing bed surface), but can't be inadvertently opened.
Created with Boxes.py (https://festi.info/boxes.py) Command line: boxes SideHingeBox Command line short: boxes SideHingeBox
